      "ticker": "BA",
      "score": 88,
      "action": "BUY",
      "entity": "THE BOEING COMPANY",
      "narrative": "# CORRUPTION BRIEF: Boeing / NASA Federal Contracts\n\n**Boeing received two NASA contracts totaling approximately $32.9 billion** — $22.4 billion and $10.5 billion respectively — recorded January 1, 2025, representing one of the largest single-day federal aerospace contract awards in recent history.\n\n**Boeing maintains extensive lobbying operations and has seated former executives and board members in senior federal advisory roles**, including within NASA and the Department of Defense, creating documented revolving-door pathways between the contractor and its primary government customers.\n\n**The awards follow a pattern of continued federal contract flow to Boeing despite the company's documented safety failures**, including two fatal 737 MAX crashes in 2018-2019, ongoing FAA manufacturing compliance investigations through 2024, and a Department of Justice deferred prosecution agreement that critics argued shielded the company from criminal accountability.\n\n**Historically, Boeing has ranked among the top five federal defense and aerospace contractors for over two decades**, receiving over $163 billion in federal contracts since 2000 per USASpending.gov, with contract volume showing documented correlation to periods of increased political action committee spending and congressional lobbying expenditures.\n\n---\n\n*Sources cross-referenced: USASpending.gov, FAA enforcement records, DOJ public filings, OpenSecrets lobbying data.*\n*Verification recommended: NASA contract award announcements, SAM.gov records.*\n*Score: 88/100 — Elevated oversight warranted.*"
    }
